''This is a VBA Macro code snippet used to sort a range of data base on the provided key.
''Example: In this snippet, I will sort a range from B8 to K1000 based on the column within E8. (Useful for Sales sorting)
''Created by: Gerald John Alviar https://ph.linkedin.com/in/geraldalviar, please contact me if you use it. This will help to improve my snippet.

Sub SortBBIN()
Range("B8:K1000").Sort _
Key1:=Range("E8"), Order1:=xlDescending 'xlAscending for Ascending order
End Sub
